'''
You will be given a number which represent your character's altitude above sea level
> Positive numbers represent height above the water.
> O is sea level.
> Negative numbers represent depth below the water's surface.
Write a program to print your current level and can you breath or not.
'''

n = int(input("Enter your current altitude: "))

if n > 0:
    print("You are above sea level")
    print("You can breathe")
elif n == 0:
    print("You are at sea level")
    print("You can breathe")
else:
    print("You are below sea level")
    print("You cannot breathe")

# OUTPUT 
'''
Enter your current altitude: 0
You are at sea level
You can breathe
'''
